- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on linguistic applications of mixed effects modeling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as mixed effects modeling is a statistical technique commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as the example used in the paper focuses on phonetic analysis of voice pitch data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as mixed effects modeling is commonly used in social network analysis. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as mixed effects modeling can be used in control systems.
